text: Plenty of very good food both, in the hawker centre and the coffee shops behind.  Famous duck rice, fishball noodle and Muslim stalls at the hawker centre.  Famous bao and prawn noodle and also chicken rice stall at the coffee shops.  All 3 are highly recommended.
Great food! It's been our go to place for quick lunch. It's near our work place.
The no-name kway chap stall is famous in this neighbourhood and is sold out b4 lunch. Have to come early in the morning to eat. 2 thumbs up.
Has a variety of food available here. Ate some dessert like beancurd and grass jelly around here. Crowded on Saturday mornings.
Notting special to eat here. The only one can try is 墩汤, but service is such. And only started business after 1pm. Don try already.
